==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[אהרן|אַהֲרֹן]] ''(Ahărōn)'', "bearer of martyrs". Also explained as 'mountaineer, enlightner'.

===Proper noun===

# A person in the [[Old Testament]], the elder brother of [[Moses]] in the Book of the [[Exodus]].
# A male [[given name]].

